    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">How to start my motion at 30º not at 0º</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">Frequently, the timing of a motion means the X-axis value of Blend-Point #1, the start of &#160;Segment #1, cannot be at </text><text styleclass="VariableName" translate="true">0</text><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true"> . </text></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">In this case you want to move </text><text styleclass="Element-Header" translate="true">Blend-Point #1</text><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true"> from 0.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">To move </text><text styleclass="Element-Header" translate="true">Blend-Point #1</text><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true"> to a value that is not 0, edit the </text><text styleclass="ParameterHeader" translate="true">Motion-Start</text><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true"> parameter in the </text><text styleclass="Element-Header" translate="true">Blend-Point Editor</text><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">. </text></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">The motion moves along the </text><text styleclass="VariableName" translate="true">X-axis</text><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true"> by the </text><text styleclass="ParameterHeader" translate="true">Motion-Start</text><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true"> parameter.</text></para>
